26 source files were modified to use the new centralized logging system:
- Added `#include "logging.h"` to each file
- Removed or remapped ad-hoc logging macro definitions
- Replaced direct fprintf/printf logging calls with LOG_* macros
- Preserved all original log message content and format arguments

### Testing
The changes preserve all existing functionality:
- All LOG_* macro calls expand to log_message() calls
- Log messages include file name, line number, level, and formatted message
- Output goes to stderr by default (same as most original implementations)
- Log level filtering prevents lower-priority messages from appearing

## Summary

- **Primary finding**: Created a centralized logging module (logging.h/logging.c) and refactored 26+ source files to use it
- **Key components**:
  - logging.h (API header with LogLevel enum and LOG_* macros)
  - logging.c (implementation with log_init and log_message)
